tafsir[8]{c,v,t}:
  28,6,"28:5"
  28,7,"وَأَوْحَيْنَا إِلَىٰ أُمِّ مُوسَىٰ (28:7) The word Wahy (inspiration) is used here in its literal meaning. It does not mean the Wahy that is peculiar to prophets. This point has already been explained under Surah Taha."
  28,8,"28:7"
